<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1086,2017]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1086,1111]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[381,462,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="77.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[225,1370,276,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@77.[194,1399,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Adults of Argyresthia spp. 36, A. (Argyresthia) cardiopetala, sp. nov., ♀, paratype; 37, A. (A.) mala, sp. nov., ♀, paratype; 38, A. (A.) longa, sp. nov., ♀, paratype; 39, A. (A.) decurtata, sp. nov., ♀, paratype; 40, A. (A.) decurtata, sp. nov., dark form, ♂, paratype; 41, A. (A.) minutisocia, sp. nov., ♀, paratype; 42, A. (A.) scalprata, sp. nov., ♂, holotype; 43, A. (A.) grammosacca, sp. nov., ♀, paratype. (Scales = 2.0 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827760/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) wingspan 10.5̄11.0 mm. Head pale yellowish white. Labial palpus white, mixed with gray on lateral surface. Antenna with scape yellowish white, pecten fuscous; flagellum grayish white, ringed with black. Foreleg blackish fuscous on inner surface, white on outer surface, tarsus blackish fuscous on distal part of each tarsomere; midleg gray on inner surface, tibia dotted with gray near base, at middle and on distal dorsally, tarsus gray on distal part of each tarsomere, remainder white; hindleg white except tibia blackish gray distally, tarsus blackish gray distally on each tarsomere. Thorax pale yellowish white; tegula dark grayish fuscous. Forewing ratio 5.0; ground color gray to dark gray, distal 1/3 densely covered with dark grayish-fuscous scales; costa with about six white transverse striae along basal 2/5, with a longitudinal rectangular dark grayish-fuscous streak from basal 2/5 to 2/3 as wide as 1/6 width of wing, with two larger dark grayish spots alternated with yellowish-white spots on distal 1/3; grayish-fuscous streak below basal half of fold; dorsal band white, extending to before tornus; dorsal fascia dark grayish fuscous, broad, from before middle of wing to near longitudinal costal streak; cilia yellowish white adjacent yellowish-white costal spot, blackish fuscous around apex, gray on termen and near tornus. Hindwing and cilia uniformly gray. Abdomen blackish gray dorsally, gray ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1086,2017]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,303,1554,1579]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Venation</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[324,395,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[215,1412,317,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[172,1416,302,1853]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Wing venation of Argyresthia spp. 1, A. (Blastotere) aureola, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12525 W, paratype; 2, A. (B.) cineretra, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12402 W, paratype; 3, A. (Argyresthia) cardiopetala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12041 W, paratype; 4, A. (A.) punctuata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12536 W, paratype; 5, A. (A.) subrimosa Meyrick, slide no. LTT 1303 W; 6, A. (A.) lanosa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12635 W, paratype; 7, A. (A.) beta Friese &amp; Moriuti, slide no. LTT 12481 W; 8, A. (A.) ellipsoidea, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12385 W, paratype. (Scales = 2.0 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827748/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
): Forewing with R1 originating from beyond basal 1/3 of upper margin of cell, R4 and R5 stalked; hindwing with M3 and CuA1 stalked.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1086,2017]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,373,1632,1657]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[391,502,1632,1657]" captionStart="FIGURES 102 – 107" captionStartId="86.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[207,1368,212,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@86.[191,1396,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="FIGURES 102 – 107. Eighth sternite and male genitalia excluding phallus of Argyresthia spp. 102, A. (Argyresthia) curvativa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12853, holotype; 103, A. (A.) atomata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12804, holotype; 104, A. (A.) orthocera, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12774, holotype; 105, A. (A.) cardiopetala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12432, paratype; 106, A. (A.) mala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12784, paratype; 107, A. (A.) longa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12493, holotype. (Scales = 0.2 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827778/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Figs. 105</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[517,561,1632,1657]" captionStart="FIGURES 158 – 161" captionStartId="98.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[213,1371,227,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@98.[191,1396,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="98" captionText="FIGURES 158 – 161. Phallus of Argyresthia spp. 158, A. (Argyresthia) curvativa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12853, holotype; 159, A. (A.) atomata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12804, holotype; 160, A. (A.) orthocera, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12774, holotype; 161, A. (A.) cardiopetala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12432, paratype. (Scales = 0.2 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827802/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">161</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[576,623,1632,1656]" captionStart="FIGURES 209 – 220" captionStartId="109.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[229,1344,195,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@109.[224,1358,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 209 – 220. Socii of Argyresthia spp. 209, A. (Argyresthia) trigonophylla, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12816, paratype; 210, A. (A.) chiotorna, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12757, paratype; 211, A. (A.) hirsuta, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12841, holotype; 212, A. (A.) papillata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12815, holotype; 213, A. (A.) acuminata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12740, holotype; 214, A. (A.) curvativa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12853, holotype; 215, A. (A.) atomata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12804, holotype; 216, A. (A.) orthocera, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12774, holotype; 217, A. (A.) cardiopetala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12432, paratype; 218, A. (A.) mala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12784, paratype; 219, A. (A.) longa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12493, holotype; 220, A. (A.) decurtata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12842, holotype. (Scales = 0.1 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827822/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">217</figureCitation>
): Tuba analis shorter than width of valva. Socius covered with 15̄23 scale-like setae, bearing two long setae posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[728,826,1668,1693]" captionStart="FIGURES 209 – 220" captionStartId="109.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[229,1344,195,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@109.[224,1358,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 209 – 220. Socii of Argyresthia spp. 209, A. (Argyresthia) trigonophylla, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12816, paratype; 210, A. (A.) chiotorna, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12757, paratype; 211, A. (A.) hirsuta, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12841, holotype; 212, A. (A.) papillata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12815, holotype; 213, A. (A.) acuminata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12740, holotype; 214, A. (A.) curvativa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12853, holotype; 215, A. (A.) atomata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12804, holotype; 216, A. (A.) orthocera, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12774, holotype; 217, A. (A.) cardiopetala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12432, paratype; 218, A. (A.) mala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12784, paratype; 219, A. (A.) longa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12493, holotype; 220, A. (A.) decurtata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12842, holotype. (Scales = 0.1 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827822/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 217</figureCitation>
). Gnathos inflated distally, with eight long thick apical setae. Valva somewhat heart-shaped, widest at basal 1/3, dorsal margin concave near apex; a clump of thick setae in disc near ventral margin. Saccus 1.6 times as long as width of valva, with distal 2/3 linear, rounded apically. Phallus straight, 5.0 times as long as width of valva (
<figureCitation box="[652,749,1776,1801]" captionStart="FIGURES 158 – 161" captionStartId="98.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[213,1371,227,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@98.[191,1396,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="98" captionText="FIGURES 158 – 161. Phallus of Argyresthia spp. 158, A. (Argyresthia) curvativa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12853, holotype; 159, A. (A.) atomata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12804, holotype; 160, A. (A.) orthocera, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12774, holotype; 161, A. (A.) cardiopetala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12432, paratype. (Scales = 0.2 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827802/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 161</figureCitation>
). Second sternite with 12̄13 micro-setae in each row; eighth sternite Y-shaped. Coremata present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1086,2017]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,396,1848,1873]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[412,511,1848,1873]" captionStart="FIGURES 265 – 267" captionStartId="117.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[297,1382,222,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@117.[177,1409,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="FIGURES 265 – 267. Female genitalia of Argyresthia spp. 265, A. (Argyresthia) curvativa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12855, paratype; 266, A. (A.) cardiopetala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12062, paratype; 267, A. (A.) mala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12506, paratype. (Scales = 0.5 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827838/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 266</figureCitation>
): Ovipositor 2.6 times as long as eighth segment. Anterior apophysis 3/5 length of posterior apophysis, bifurcate at distal 2/5, branches fused, forming ventral margin of ostium bursae. Lamella postvaginalis subrectangular. Antrum funnel-shaped, 2/7 length of eighth segment; ductus seminalis not observed. Corpus bursae oval, with dense micro-denticles on posterior 1/3; signum with basal 3/4 band-shaped, slightly widened from basal 2/3 to 3/4, with a transverse ridge beyond basal 3/4, then narrowed triangularly.
</paragraph>
